{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nFlipping `identity.require_authenticated` with a wrong or self-referential `enforce_since`\nwould either fail the gate on legitimate historical unsigned events, or be impossible to pin\n(the boundary cannot be the flip commit — the flip is a code commit on `main`, whereas\n`enforce_since` is a ref on the `tickets` tracker branch, and it must exist *before* it is\nreferenced). This story remediates the grandfathering check and **decides** the boundary\nanchor; it does **not** write it (the atomic-flip story 8d39 writes `enforce_since` exactly\nonce, so there is no double-write).\n\n## What\n\n- **Verify the grandfathering logic** in `src/rebar/_commands/verify_authorship.py` and\n  `src/rebar/_config_schema.py`: `_is_enforced(commit_sha, since_ref, tracker)`\n  (`verify_authorship.py:262-282`) enforces an event iff its introducing commit is `since_ref`\n  or a descendant (`git merge-base --is-ancestor <since_ref> <commit>` exit 0), fail-closed;\n  `grandfathered = not enforced` is emitted per non-verified event (`:500-521`); the run exits\n  non-zero iff `required` and `enforced_not_verified > 0` (`:464`, `:542-559`). `enforce_since`\n  is the `identity.enforce_since` config key (`_config_schema.py:336-342`, coerced `_as_str`\n  `:580`), overridable by `--since` / `REBAR_IDENTITY_ENFORCE_SINCE` (`verify_authorship.py:465`).\n- **Add a regression test** (`tests/unit/test_identity_enforce_since_<slug>.py`) that closes the\n  coverage gaps the held-out oracle leaves: drive the boundary through the **config/env path**\n  (`identity.enforce_since` / `REBAR_IDENTITY_ENFORCE_SINCE`), not just the `--since` flag, and\n  assert per-event `grandfathered` flags in a **single mixed store**. It builds one temp store\n  with a pre-boundary unsigned event AND a post-boundary unsigned/forged in-scope event, sets\n  the boundary between them, and asserts: overall exit non-zero (post-boundary enforced), the\n  pre-boundary entry has `grandfathered: true`, the post-boundary entry `grandfathered: false`;\n  plus a second store with only the pre-boundary unsigned event asserting exit 0. Uses the\n  established harness (`repo` fixture, `_keypair`, forge recipe, in-process\n  `verify_authorship.cli`). Proving command: `make test` (the new test passes).\n- **Decide and document the enforcement-boundary anchor**: an **existing** `tickets`-branch\n  commit at which write-signing is confirmed live across **all** writers (local 79da, CI 4dc0,\n  Gerrit-side 1a51). Method: after those three stories confirm signing, take a candidate anchor\n  = current `tickets` HEAD and verify `rebar verify-identity --all --require-authenticated\n  --since <candidate>` exits 0 (zero enforced-unverified events); if any enforced-unverified\n  event descends from the candidate, advance past it (or fix that writer) and re-check. Record\n  the chosen 40-hex SHA + rationale on this ticket for 8d39 to consume verbatim.\n\n## Scope\n\nThe grandfathering boundary check + a regression test + the boundary decision/rationale.\nWriting `enforce_since` into `rebar.toml` and the flag flip both belong to 8d39 — this story\ndoes **not** modify `rebar.toml` (verified: the change touches only the new test file under\n`tests/`). `file_impact`: the new test file.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] **The chosen anchor grandfathers all pre-boundary history.**\n      `rebar verify-identity --all --require-authenticated --since <anchor>` exits 0 (zero\n      enforced, non-verified events; every event at/before the anchor is grandfathered).\n- [ ] **A regression test asserts both directions.** A synthetic **unsigned** event before the\n      boundary PASSES (grandfathered, gate exit 0) and a new unsigned/forged in-scope event\n      after the boundary FAILS (enforced, non-zero) — driven via the `identity.enforce_since`\n      config/env path and asserting the per-event `grandfathered` flag. Proving command:\n      `make test` runs green (and the specific new test:\n      `pytest tests/unit/test_identity_enforce_since_<slug>.py -q` exits 0).\n- [ ] **The anchor is chosen and recorded; `rebar.toml` is untouched.** Let `A` = the decided\n      40-hex boundary SHA (an **existing** `tickets`-branch commit, NOT the flip commit).\n      Proving commands: `git -C .tickets-tracker cat-file -t \"$A\"` prints `commit` (the anchor\n      exists on the tickets branch); a comment on this ticket records `A` + its rationale\n      (`rebar show 8d91-5103-ae1b-44a7 | jq -e --arg s \"$A\" '[.comments[].body]|any(contains($s))'`\n      exits 0); and `git diff --stat origin/main..HEAD -- rebar.toml` shows no change (this\n      story's change touches only the new test file)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784238786368036001,"uuid":"996db446-d969-4da6-9de2-142eef0d1286"}